<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a12098e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6556"><num value="6556">§ 6556.</num><heading> Termination of effectiveness</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The authority provided by this subchapter terminates effective <date date="2023-10-01">October 1, 2023</date>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a12098f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/108/148/tIV/s406">Pub. L. 108–148, title IV, § 406</ref>, <date date="2003-12-03">Dec. 3, 2003</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/117/1911">117 Stat. 1911</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/115/334/tVIII/s8406/a">Pub. L. 115–334, title VIII, § 8406(a)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-20">Dec. 20, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4845">132 Stat. 4845</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7a120990-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7a120991-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id7a120992-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2018—<ref href="/us/pl/115/334">Pub. L. 115–334</ref> amended section generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “There are authorized to be appropriated such sums as are necessary to carry out this subchapter for each of fiscal years 2004 through 2008.”</p>
